"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751811","Department of Health","false","2017-07-18","<p>This information is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>The Department collects total spending on agency and contract staff by National Health Service trust. It is not possible to separate accident and emergency departments from other departments, nor doctors from other staff groups.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-07-18T14:42:22.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751811/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751811/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751811/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-07-13","Locums: Accident and Emergency Departments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the total spending on locum doctors in accident and emergency departments, by NHS trust, was in each of the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","4862"
