"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751192","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-21","<p>The Government has not issued guidance for local authorities on this matter. It is for each local authority to decide for itself what arrangements it should put in place.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2017-07-21T09:53:50.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751192/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751192/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751192/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-12",,"2","House of Lords","Her Majesty's Government what guidance is available for local authorities on the arrangements they should make in the event that a chief executive stands down temporarily.","false","Biography information for Lord Storey",,"Lord Storey","HL789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751193","Attorney General","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Government is committed to strengthening the UK's response to bribery, corruption, money laundering, fraud and other forms of economic crime.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is continuing to review options to improve the effectiveness of the UK's response to economic crime, and any measures resulting from this work will be announced in due course.</p><p> </p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2017-07-17T16:27:18.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751193/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751193/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751193/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2017-07-12","Banks: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what assessment he has made of the effect of proposals to move the functions of the Serious Fraud Office to the National Crime Agency on criminality in the banking sector.","false","Biography information for Mhairi Black","Paisley and Renfrewshire South","Mhairi Black","4613"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751194","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-19","<p>Pursuant to the Answer of 3 July 2017 to Question 2657, the modus operandi of the coordination committee will be agreed between the Conservative party and the Democratic Unionist party.</p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2017-07-19T12:03:23.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751194/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751194/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751194/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-12","Coordination Committee","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 3 July 2017 to Question 2657, on the Democratic Unionist Party, if he will publish the names of those hon. Members who attend each meeting of the Coordination Committee; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","4679"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751195","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-17","<p>As set out in the Conservative manifesto, although comprehensive reform is not a priority, we are committed to ensure that the House of Lords continues to fulfil its constitutional role as a revising and scrutinising chamber which respects the primacy of the House of Commons. We will continue to work to ensure the work of the House of Lords remains relevant and effective by addressing issues such as its size.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","4531","2017-07-17T15:28:38.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751195/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751195/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751195/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-12","Hereditary Peers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what plans he has for removing hereditary peers from the House of Lords.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr  Dan Poulter","4530"
