"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751200","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-17","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-07-17T15:36:20.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751200/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751200/answer","PQ4512 FINAL.pdf","PQ4512 FINAL.pdf","UKSA Response to PQ4512","UKSA Response to PQ4512","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751200/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-12","Electoral Register: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many eligible electors are not registered to vote in (a) the Arfon constituency and (b) Wales.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","4512"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751201","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-21","<p>We do not comment on commercial deals or the costs as the UK Government needs to retain commercial sensitivity and competitive tension in order to secure the best deal for the taxpayer in other locations.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) will be the major occupier, taking up around 90 per cent of available space. New Waverley will be a significant part of HMRC’s transformation to become a smaller, more highly-skilled operation fit for the digital age and able to deliver a better and more modern service at lower cost to the taxpayer.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>It will contribute to overall savings for the taxpayer of more than £300 million up to 2025, and after 2025 deliver annual cost savings of more than £90 million. Alongside the cost savings the programme will deliver value for money through wider benefits; co-locating teams in a large office will enable collaborative working across government, sharing of expertise, promotion and career development without the need to move.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","4590 ; 4594","2017-07-21T11:09:17.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751201/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751201/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751201/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-12","Cabinet Office: Edinburgh","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what forecast he has made of the fit-out and running costs of HMG New Waverley.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","4588"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751202","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-21","<p>The requirement for a public interface will be determined by the operational needs of Departments.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-07-21T11:15:49.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751202/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751202/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751202/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-12","Cabinet Office: Edinburgh","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether he plans that HMG New Waverley will have a public interface.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","4589"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751203","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-21","<p>The UK Government was advised by JLL on suitable sites for the Edinburgh Hub and New Waverley was found to be the most suitable, measured against numerous criteria, as well as cost efficiency.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-07-21T11:12:27.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751203/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751203/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751203/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-12","Cabinet Office: Edinburgh","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what procurement process was used to decide on New Waverley as the location for a Government hub.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","4591"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751204","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-21","<p>The first teams from HMRC will move into New Waverley from summer 2020.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-07-21T11:13:30.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751204/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751204/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751204/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-12","Cabinet Office: Edinburgh","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when he plans that HMG New Waverley will open.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","4592"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751205","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-21","<p>With the exception of HMRC, we are not naming departments publicly at this stage to ensure they are able to properly consult and communicate with their staff.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-07-21T11:14:33.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751205/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751205/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751205/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-12","Cabinet Office: Edinburgh","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which Government Departments he plans will have staff at HMG New Waverley.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","4593"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751206","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-21","<p>We do not comment on commercial deals or the costs as the UK Government needs to retain commercial sensitivity and competitive tension in order to secure the best deal for the taxpayer in other locations.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) will be the major occupier, taking up around 90 per cent of available space. New Waverley will be a significant part of HMRC’s transformation to become a smaller, more highly-skilled operation fit for the digital age and able to deliver a better and more modern service at lower cost to the taxpayer.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>It will contribute to overall savings for the taxpayer of more than £300 million up to 2025, and after 2025 deliver annual cost savings of more than £90 million. Alongside the cost savings the programme will deliver value for money through wider benefits; co-locating teams in a large office will enable collaborative working across government, sharing of expertise, promotion and career development without the need to move.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","4588 ; 4594","2017-07-21T11:09:17.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751206/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751206/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751206/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-12","Cabinet Office: Edinburgh","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the capital costs that will be associated with HMG New Waverley.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","4590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751207","Cabinet Office","false","2017-07-21","<p>We do not comment on commercial deals or the costs as the UK Government needs to retain commercial sensitivity and competitive tension in order to secure the best deal for the taxpayer in other locations.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) will be the major occupier, taking up around 90 per cent of available space. New Waverley will be a significant part of HMRC’s transformation to become a smaller, more highly-skilled operation fit for the digital age and able to deliver a better and more modern service at lower cost to the taxpayer.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>It will contribute to overall savings for the taxpayer of more than £300 million up to 2025, and after 2025 deliver annual cost savings of more than £90 million. Alongside the cost savings the programme will deliver value for money through wider benefits; co-locating teams in a large office will enable collaborative working across government, sharing of expertise, promotion and career development without the need to move.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","4588 ; 4590","2017-07-21T11:09:17.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751207/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751207/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751207/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-07-12","Cabinet Office: Edinburgh","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the cost is of lease payments for HMG New Waverley under the recently-signed agreement to lease its premises over the life of that lease.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","4594"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751208","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-19","<p>The Government is determined that everyone who is entitled to the National Minimum Wage (NMW) and National Living Wage (NLW) receives it. Anyone who feels they have been underpaid NMW or NLW should contact the Acas helpline on 0300 123 1100. HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) review all complaints that are referred to them.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC does not record statistics on complaints or investigations by reference to countries of the United Kingdom, Government regions, constituencies or counties. Since 1999, when NMW enforcement began, HMRC has identified over 25,500 employers with total NMW arrears of almost £79 million. Last year (2016/17) HMRC identified over 1,100 employers with total NMW arrears of over £10.9 million.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC cannot comment on the affairs of individual taxpayers, as it has a duty to maintain taxpayer confidentiality. However, the Department for Business for Energy and Industrial Strategy (BEIS) run a naming scheme for employers who are found to have underpaid NMW. You can find more information at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/enforcing-national-minimum-wage-law" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/enforcing-national-minimum-wage-law</a></p><p> </p><p>I refer the honourable member to the answer provided on 18<sup>th</sup> July 2016, at UIN 42723, for information on prosecution results.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","4274","2017-07-19T15:03:56.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751208/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751208/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751208/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Minimum Wage: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number of employers in Wales who were successfully prosecuted for paying less than the minimum wage in each year for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","4482"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751209","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Treasury does not collect data relating to bank branch closures.</p><p> </p><p>Decisions on the opening and closing of individual bank branches are taken by the management team of each bank on a commercial basis without intervention from Government. While banks and building societies need to balance customer interests, market competition, and other commercial factors when considering their strategy, the Government is pleased to see that the industry is committing to further improvements to protect those affected by branch closures. For this reason, the Government welcomed the industry-wide Access to Banking Protocol and Professor Russel Griggs’ independent ‘one year on’ review, published last November.</p><p> </p><p>Building on Professor Griggs’ review, the new Access to Banking Standard came into effect on 1 May. The Standard commits banks to ensure customers are better informed about branch closures and the reasons for them closing, along with the options they have locally to continue to access banking services, including specialist assistance for customers who need more help.</p><p> </p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","4499 ; 4501","2017-07-17T11:04:30.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751209/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751209/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751209/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Banks: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many bank branches have closed by parliamentary constituency in each year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","4500"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751210","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-19","<p>HM Treasury has over 10 personnel located at two locations in the UK, they are:</p><p> </p><p>1 Horse Guards Road</p><p>London</p><p>SW1A 2HQ</p><p> </p><p>Rosebery Court</p><p>St Andrews Business Park</p><p>Norwich</p><p>NR7 OHS</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-07-19T14:50:38.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751210/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751210/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751210/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Treasury: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will list all of his Department's premises in the UK by region and nation which have over 10 personnel.","false","Biography information for Stewart Hosie","Dundee East","Stewart Hosie","4481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751211","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-20","<p>The government recognises that there are different views on the merits of introducing a duty of care for financial services providers. The government welcomes the Financial Conduct Authority’s commitment to publish a discussion paper to explore the issue of duty of care, as part of the planned review of their Handbook described in their Mission document published in April.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-07-20T14:13:04.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751211/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751211/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751211/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Financial Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if the Government will introduce a requirement on the Financial Conduct Authority to set out a reasonable duty of care for financial services providers to exercise towards their customers.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","4474"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751212","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Treasury does not collect data relating to bank branch closures.</p><p> </p><p>Decisions on the opening and closing of individual bank branches are taken by the management team of each bank on a commercial basis without intervention from Government. While banks and building societies need to balance customer interests, market competition, and other commercial factors when considering their strategy, the Government is pleased to see that the industry is committing to further improvements to protect those affected by branch closures. For this reason, the Government welcomed the industry-wide Access to Banking Protocol and Professor Russel Griggs’ independent ‘one year on’ review, published last November.</p><p> </p><p>Building on Professor Griggs’ review, the new Access to Banking Standard came into effect on 1 May. The Standard commits banks to ensure customers are better informed about branch closures and the reasons for them closing, along with the options they have locally to continue to access banking services, including specialist assistance for customers who need more help.</p><p> </p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","4500 ; 4501","2017-07-17T11:04:30.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751212/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751212/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751212/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Banks: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many bank and building society branches have closed in (a) Vale of Clwyd constituency, (b) Denbighshire and (c) Conwy county in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","4499"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751213","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-20","<p>The Office for National Statistics (ONS) estimate that total pay increased by 1.8% on the year in the three months to May. In their Spring Budget Forecast, the Office for Budget Responsibility (OBR) also expected wages to increase in each year of their forecast.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is taking action to support incomes. This includes increasing the National Living Wage, raising the personal allowance and freezing fuel duty.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-07-20T14:30:48.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751213/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751213/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751213/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department has commissioned research into the effect of wage stagnation on household incomes throughout the UK.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","4472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751214","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-20","<p>Information on the Making Tax Digital (MTD) rollout was given in my written statement to the House on 13 July which is available here.</p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statements/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;use-dates=True&amp;answered-from=2017-07-13&amp;answered-to=2017-07-13&amp;dept=14&amp;uin=HCWS47" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statements/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;use-dates=True&amp;answered-from=2017-07-13&amp;answered-to=2017-07-13&amp;dept=14&amp;uin=HCWS47</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Businesses who require help to transition to MTD will be able to access the full range of support that HMRC provides to its customers to help them engage digitally.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-20T14:05:00.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751214/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751214/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751214/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Taxation: Electronic Government","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assistance will be provided to businesses transitioning to Making Tax Digital.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","4473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751215","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>As of 12<sup>th</sup> of July, over 150,000 people had applied for an eligibility code for 30 hours free childcare and over 120,000 had been successful.</p><p> </p><p>The system is designed so that most eligible parents will receive an eligibility decision and 30 hours code within 30 seconds. In some cases additional checks are needed to determine whether a parent is eligible and, where appropriate, a code will be issued following those checks.</p><p> </p><p>It is not possible to provide a definitive number of applications not completed due to technical issues as the service allows parents to part complete their application, save it and return to it later. A dedicated helpline is in place to support parents who encounter technical difficulties or delays in receiving their code.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-07-17T16:46:37.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751215/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751215/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751215/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people have applied for an eligibility childcare code for 30 hours free childcare via the gov.uk website; how many of those applications have been successful; how many of those applications have not been completed due to technical issues; and what the average amount of time was between completing that application and receiving an eligibility code.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","4504"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751216","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>Insurance Premium Tax (IPT) is a tax on insurance premiums which is accounted for and paid by insurers.</p><p> </p><p>The HMRC costing for the increase to the rate of IPT, published at Autumn Statement 2016, took into account behavioural responses resulting from any change associated to prices of general insurance products.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-17T15:29:44.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751216/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751216/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751216/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Insurance Premium Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether an assessment has been made of the potential effect of increasing insurance premium tax on the uptake of household insurance.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","4505"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751217","Department for Education","false","2017-07-18","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the Statement made by my Rt hon. Friend, the Secretary of State for Education on 17 July 2017.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-07-18T16:48:02.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751217/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751217/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751217/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-12","Schools: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much of the funding for new free schools and new selective schools allocated for future financial years will be made available to the Department for Education; and for what purposes that funding will be allocated.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","4492"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751218","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-18","<p>The Office for Budget Responsibility (OBR) expect inflation to average 2.4% over 2017 and 2.3% over 2018. Their forecast was reflected in HMT’s distributional analysis published alongside Spring Budget 2017, which illustrates how changes to tax, welfare, and spending policy impact upon households of different incomes.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is taking action to support the lowest income households. This includes increasing the National Living Wage, raising the personal allowance, and freezing fuel duty.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-07-18T11:45:13.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751218/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751218/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751218/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Inflation: Low Incomes","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department has commissioned research into the effect of inflation on low-income households.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","4471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751219","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>The government aims to have a tax system that is simple to understand and easy to comply with.</p><p> </p><p>In 2010 we set up the Office of Tax Simplification (OTS) as an independent Office of the Treasury to provide advice on how to simplify the tax system. The OTS was made permanent and statutory in 2016. This ensures it is in the best possible position to provide robust advice to the Chancellor on simplifying the tax system.</p><p> </p><p>The OTS has made over 400 recommendations to simplify the tax system, over half of which have already been implemented by the Government.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-17T15:27:12.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751219/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751219/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751219/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he plans for the simplification of the tax system; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","4524"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751220","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) will always ensure that its action is proportionate and the precise action taken will depend on the facts and circumstances of each individual case.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC have stringent governance arrangements in place where insolvency is considered. However, anyone who anticipates problems paying their tax bill should contact HMRC, who may be able to offer extra time to pay based on individual circumstances. HMRC has an outstanding record for supporting those facing genuine difficulty paying their Accelerated Payments.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC treat unpaid Accelerated Payments as any other established debt using their range of debt collection powers as necessary to recover what is owed, including insolvency powers where appropriate.</p><p> </p><p>To date, HMRC have issued 12 winding up petitions to companies with Accelerated Payment debt. Most of these companies also have non Accelerated Payment related debts.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","4526 ; 4527 ; 4528 ; 4529","2017-07-17T15:12:43.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751220/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751220/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751220/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether HM Revenue and Customs conducts a cost-benefit analysis of potential job losses and tax revenues forgone before issuing winding-up petitions for unpaid debts under accelerated payment notices.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","4525"
