"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751223","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) will always ensure that its action is proportionate and the precise action taken will depend on the facts and circumstances of each individual case.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC have stringent governance arrangements in place where insolvency is considered. However, anyone who anticipates problems paying their tax bill should contact HMRC, who may be able to offer extra time to pay based on individual circumstances. HMRC has an outstanding record for supporting those facing genuine difficulty paying their Accelerated Payments.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC treat unpaid Accelerated Payments as any other established debt using their range of debt collection powers as necessary to recover what is owed, including insolvency powers where appropriate.</p><p> </p><p>To date, HMRC have issued 12 winding up petitions to companies with Accelerated Payment debt. Most of these companies also have non Accelerated Payment related debts.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","4525 ; 4526 ; 4527 ; 4529","2017-07-17T15:12:44.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751223/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751223/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751223/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what criteria HM Revenue and Customs applies in deciding whether to issue a winding-up petition for an unpaid accelerated payment notice.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","4528"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751224","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) will always ensure that its action is proportionate and the precise action taken will depend on the facts and circumstances of each individual case.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC have stringent governance arrangements in place where insolvency is considered. However, anyone who anticipates problems paying their tax bill should contact HMRC, who may be able to offer extra time to pay based on individual circumstances. HMRC has an outstanding record for supporting those facing genuine difficulty paying their Accelerated Payments.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC treat unpaid Accelerated Payments as any other established debt using their range of debt collection powers as necessary to recover what is owed, including insolvency powers where appropriate.</p><p> </p><p>To date, HMRC have issued 12 winding up petitions to companies with Accelerated Payment debt. Most of these companies also have non Accelerated Payment related debts.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","4525 ; 4526 ; 4527 ; 4528","2017-07-17T15:12:44.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751224/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751224/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751224/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many winding-up petitions have been issued to companies in respect of accelerated payment notices issued by HM revenue and Customs in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","4529"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751225","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-18","<p>The Treasury has not made an assessment of the potential effect of a rise in interest rates on mortgage possessions.</p><p> </p><p>However, affordability requirements imposed by the Bank of England’s Financial Policy Committee (FPC) require lenders to conduct an interest rate ‘stress test’ on all new mortgage loans. The requirement ensures that all borrowers must be able to afford their mortgage repayments if, at any point over the first five years of the loan, their mortgage rate were to be 3 percentage points higher than the reversion rate (SVR) specified in the mortgage contract at origination.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, the FPC also requires regulators to ensure that mortgage lenders do not extend more than 15% of new mortgages at loan to income multiples (LTI) at or greater than 4.5.</p><p> </p><p>These measures insure against the risk of a significant increase in the number of indebted households in the case of an interest rate rise. For this reason, a rise in interest rates would not be expected to significantly increase the number of mortgage repossessions.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-07-18T11:46:55.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751225/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751225/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751225/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Mortgages: Repossession Orders","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the potential effect of a rise in interest rates on mortgage repossessions.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","4457"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751226","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-20","<p>Based on data from the Office of National Statistics, household debt-to-income ratio was 145% in Q1 2017. This is notably below the pre-crisis high of 160% in Q1 2008.</p><p> </p><p>The independent Financial Policy Committee (FPC) was set up by the government to assess and mitigate financial stability risks, including from household debt. The FPC has taken action to ensure against a significant rise in highly indebted households.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-07-20T14:27:08.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751226/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751226/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751226/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the level of personal debt is; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","4458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751227","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Treasury does not collect data relating to bank branch closures.</p><p> </p><p>Decisions on the opening and closing of individual bank branches are taken by the management team of each bank on a commercial basis without intervention from Government. While banks and building societies need to balance customer interests, market competition, and other commercial factors when considering their strategy, the Government is pleased to see that the industry is committing to further improvements to protect those affected by branch closures. For this reason, the Government welcomed the industry-wide Access to Banking Protocol and Professor Russel Griggs’ independent ‘one year on’ review, published last November.</p><p> </p><p>Building on Professor Griggs’ review, the new Access to Banking Standard came into effect on 1 May. The Standard commits banks to ensure customers are better informed about branch closures and the reasons for them closing, along with the options they have locally to continue to access banking services, including specialist assistance for customers who need more help.</p><p> </p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","4499 ; 4500","2017-07-17T11:04:30.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751227/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751227/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751227/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Banks: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect of bank and building society closures on (a) town centres, (b) businesses and (c) individuals.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","4501"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751228","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>Information on the Making Tax Digital rollout was given in my written statement to the House on 13 July which is available here.</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statements/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;use-dates=True&amp;answered-from=2017-07-13&amp;answered-to=2017-07-13&amp;dept=14&amp;uin=HCWS47" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statements/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;use-dates=True&amp;answered-from=2017-07-13&amp;answered-to=2017-07-13&amp;dept=14&amp;uin=HCWS47</a></p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-17T15:02:50.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751228/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751228/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751228/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Taxation: Electronic Government","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will phase in digital taxation rollout.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","4503"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751229","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-18","<p>The Welsh Government receives funding from a variety of sources. The Welsh Government’s own spending plans will set out this in detail.</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://gov.wales/funding/budget/final-budget-2017-18/?lang=en" target="_blank">http://gov.wales/funding/budget/final-budget-2017-18/?lang=en</a></p><p> </p><p>Details of the Welsh Government’s Block Grant are set out in tables 1.6 and 1.7 of the 2017 Spring Budget document.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/597467/spring_budget_2017_web.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/597467/spring_budget_2017_web.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>The 2016 Country and Regional Analysis contains details of all identifiable public expenditure by the UK Government, Welsh Government and Local Authorities in Wales.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/569815/Country_and_Regional_Analysis_November_2016.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/569815/Country_and_Regional_Analysis_November_2016.pdf</a></p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-07-18T13:24:20.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751229/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751229/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751229/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Public Expenditure: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what funds had been allocated to Wales up to 2020 before the decision for the UK to leave the EU was made.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","4489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751230","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>During the last Parliament the Government announced over 35 measures and invested a further £800 million in HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) to tackle avoidance and evasion.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC investigate all instances of tax avoidance and have robust compliance procedures in place to take action against any identified abuse.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-17T15:04:58.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751230/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751230/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751230/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of HM Revenue and Customs's ability to investigate whether there are grounds for it to recover tax revenue lost to alleged tax avoidance schemes promoted by the Anderson Group and other temporary recruitment agencies; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","4623"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751231","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-20","<p>As part of the process of reviewing the Inter-Governmental Agreement between the UK and the US that implements FATCA in the UK, my officials have raised a wide range of issues with the US Treasury and the IRS, including the obligations placed by the US on the non-life insurance industry.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","4702 ; 4703","2017-07-20T14:03:52.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751231/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751231/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751231/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Tax Avoidance: USA","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with his US counterpart on (a) that country repealing its Foreign Account Tax Compliance Act and (b) exempting non-life insurance services from the remit of that Act.","false","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","4634"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751232","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>The independent Office for Budget Responsibility (OBR) is tasked with creating the forecasts for economic growth on which the government sets fiscal policy. These are published in the ‘Economic and fiscal outlook’, most recently at the Spring Budget 2017. At Spring Budget 2017, the OBR revised up growth in 2017 to 2.0%, but revised it slightly down thereafter.</p><p> </p><p>There are no official projections of inequality. The latest data from the Office for National Statistics show that inequality reached a 30-yr low last year.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-07-17T11:19:48.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751232/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751232/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751232/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Economic Growth: Inequality","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department has commissioned research on projected levels of inequality and economic growth.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","4644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751233","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>The government is committed to supporting all those affected by problem debt, and has a range of measures in place.</p><p> </p><p>The Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) regulates the consumer credit market, and has introduced binding rules to strengthen consumer protection. They are based on the principle that money should only be lent to a consumer if they can afford to repay it; lenders must show forbearance if there is evidence of financial difficulty.</p><p> </p><p>The FCA also capped the cost of payday loans. As part of a review of this price cap, the FCA will examine the high-cost credit market more broadly (such as rent-to-own), and consider whether further interventions are necessary to address the risk of consumer harm.</p><p> </p><p>The Money Advice Service (MAS) coordinates the provision of free-to-client debt advice. Last financial year, MAS had a debt advice budget of £45m and funded 380,000 free-to-client debt advice sessions.</p><p> </p><p>In the Queen’s Speech, the government announced the Financial Guidance and Claims Bill. This will legislate to restructure the financial guidance landscape and bring debt advice, money guidance, and pensions guidance together in a single body, and give consumers better access to the financial information they need. This Bill is currently going through Parliament.</p><p> </p><p>This government's manifesto proposed a statutory breathing space that would give heavily indebted consumers a period of respite from enforcement action, and further interest and charges for a period of up to six weeks. Where appropriate, this would be followed by a statutory repayment plan to help them pay back their debts in a sustainable way. We will outline further information on how this policy could be implemented in due course.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-07-17T10:46:54.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751233/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751233/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751233/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Debts: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps his Department is taking to prevent young people from falling into problem debt.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","4645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751234","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-20","<p>The cross government Surge and Rapid Response Team (SRRT) is available to all government departments to provide assistance with unexpected demands for access to their services and provide operational support in a crisis situation. The team is hosted by HMRC. During 2016/17, SRRT provided support to Border Force at Heathrow Airport between July and October, with resource ranging from 9 to 44 FTE per week during that period. Staff provided assistance with a range of border control operations after receiving full training from Border Force.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-20T14:06:40.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751234/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751234/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751234/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Revenue and Customs: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what support HM Revenue and Customs' Surge and Rapid Response Team provides to Border Force.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","4611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751235","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Treasury has not made any formal assessment of the economic effect of immigration enforcement on business.</p><p> </p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-07-17T11:05:34.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751235/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751235/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751235/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Economic Situation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the economic effect of the enforcement of immigration policy on businesses in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","4656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751236","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>Government has not made an estimate of the number of cash machines that would be removed or start charging customers if business rates were levied on cash machines.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-07-17T11:21:40.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751236/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751236/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751236/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Cash Dispensing: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the proportion of free-to-use cash machines which would (a) be removed or (b) start charging customers if business rates are levied on cash machines.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","4658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751237","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-20","<p>The Government introduced the higher rates of stamp duty on additional properties to support home ownership and first-time buyers. It is right that people should be free to purchase a second home or invest in a buy-to-let property, but the Government is aware that this can impact on other people’s ability to get on to the property ladder.</p><p> </p><p>The latest estimate for this measure’s receipts for 2016-17 is £1.6 billion, compared to an initial forecast of £0.7 billion.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-20T14:09:44.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751237/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751237/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751237/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Stamp Duty Land Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment he has made of the effect of the stamp duty levy on investment in new homes to rent out.","false","Biography information for James Gray","North Wiltshire","James Gray","4669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751238","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-20","<p>Estimated receipts from the higher rate of SDLT on ‘additional properties’ from 1 April 2016, is published in 'Quarterly Stamp Duty Statistics' Table 6.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/quarterly-stamp-duty-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/quarterly-stamp-duty-statistics</a></p><p> </p><p>Statistics on repayments from the higher rate of SDLT on additional properties for 2016-17 are due to be published in July 2017.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-20T14:08:49.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751238/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751238/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751238/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Stamp Duty Land Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the total income from the additional stamp duty levy on additional homes was for 2016-17; and what the total amount refunded was on the grounds of a purchaser having sold their main residence within three years of buying a new one.","false","Biography information for James Gray","North Wiltshire","James Gray","4670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751239","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-20","<p>The key assumptions behind the forecast for expected revenue from the SDLT higher rates for additional properties are set out in the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015 policy costings:</p><p> </p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/480565/SRAS2015_policy_costings_amended_page_25.pdf</p><p>These assumptions were updated in the Budget 2016 policy costings:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/508147/PU1912_Policy_Costings_FINAL3.pdf</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-20T14:07:56.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751239/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751239/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751239/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Stamp Duty Land Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assumptions he made in forecasting expected revenue from the three percentage point stamp duty levy on the purchase of additional homes and homes to rent out.","false","Biography information for James Gray","North Wiltshire","James Gray","4671"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751240","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>There are no plans for HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) to routinely provide unearned income information.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC provides information to the Child Maintenance Service (CMS) to help in the calculation of child maintenance payments. This is provided on a request basis in line with DWP legislation. HMRC routinely shares earned income information which covers the vast majority of individuals.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC is committed to working with DWP, the CMS and others to improve data flows to best support the calculation and collection of child maintenance.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-17T15:25:43.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751240/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751240/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751240/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Child Maintenance Service","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether there are plans for HM Revenue and Customs to routinely share data on the unearned income of non-resident parents with the Child Maintenance Service as an alternative to the request-led system.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre  Brock","4741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751241","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Government does not intend to publish the research it conducted earlier in the year on the effects of transparency in overseas money transfers (involving foreign exchange) on consumer decisions at this point in time as it relates to the formulation and development of ongoing government policy.</p><p> </p><p>However, the research will help to inform the Government’s response to its consultation on the implementation of the second Payment Services Directive, which will be published shortly. The Government will need to weigh up the benefits of requiring greater transparency with other considerations, such as the Government’s approach to implementing maximum harmonising Directives.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-07-17T14:01:45.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751241/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751241/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751241/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-07-12","Foreign Exchange","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he plans to publish the results of the research on foreign exchange; whether those results will be published with the Government response to that consultation; whether he plans to use those results to inform amendments to the draft Payment Services Regulations 2017; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","4713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751242","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-20","<p>It is the landlord’s responsibility to ensure that people are safe, and cost considerations should not get in the way of this. Where work is necessary to ensure the fire safety of social housing, we will ensure that lack of financial resources will not prevent it going ahead.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-20T15:26:45.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751242/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751242/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751242/answer","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751242/answer/previousversion/5097","Biography information for Alok Sharma","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-12","High Rise Flats: Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 11 July 2017 to Question 2992, whether he plans that the resources to ensure the fire safety of social housing will be made available based on new fire safety regulations arising out of the Grenfell Tower fire or on existing fire regulations.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","4750"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751243","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Local Government and Social Care Ombudsman, which is independent of both central and local government, investigates complaints by individuals about local public services and all registerable social care providers throughout England, and can make recommendations for redress. Ministers meet the Ombudsman from time to time, and discuss a range of matters relating to the work of the organisation.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","4622","2017-07-17T16:31:23.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751243/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751243/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751243/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-12","Local Government and Social Care Ombudsman","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what discussions he has had with the Local Government and Social Care Ombudsman on ensuring that the requirements within the Data Protection Act 1998 are upheld by the organisations within his remit.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","4621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751244","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-18","<p>Our statement of 6 July set out the approach we are adopting.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/expert-panel-recommends-further-tests-on-cladding-and-insulation" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/expert-panel-recommends-further-tests-on-cladding-and-insulation</a></p><p>The 2 insulation materials recommended by the expert panel for use in the full testing were rigid polyisocyanurate foam (PIR) and non-combustible mineral wool. There are many types of rigid foam insulation boards available and PIR was considered to be the most appropriate option for purposes of this series of tests.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-18T16:21:30.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751244/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751244/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751244/answer","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751244/answer/previousversion/5095","Biography information for Alok Sharma","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-12","Fire Prevention: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to include phenolic foam in fire safety tests of cladding and insulation materials being undertaken in response to the Grenfell Tower fire.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","4620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751245","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Local Government and Social Care Ombudsman, which is independent of both central and local government, investigates complaints by individuals about local public services and all registerable social care providers throughout England, and can make recommendations for redress. Ministers meet the Ombudsman from time to time, and discuss a range of matters relating to the work of the organisation.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","4621","2017-07-17T16:31:23.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751245/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751245/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751245/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-12","Local Government and Social Care Ombudsman","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what discussions he has had with the Local Government and Social Care Ombudsman on ensuring that the requirements within the Equality Act 2010 are upheld by the organisations within his remit.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","4622"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751246","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-07-17","<p>There are no plans to reinstate the contaminated land capital grants programme.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-07-17T16:46:13.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751246/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751246/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751246/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-07-12","Land: Contamination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether he has plans to reinstate the contaminated land capital grants programme.","false","Biography information for Mrs Pauline Latham","Mid Derbyshire","Pauline Latham","4701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751247","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-17","<p>The Government has a Manifesto commitment to continue to give local government greater control over the money they raise locally. We will collaborate closely with local government over the coming months about how we achieve this, including through revenue support grant and business rates.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-07-17T15:21:59.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751247/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751247/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751247/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-12","Revenue Support Grant: Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether he plans to replace the rate support grant with business rates.","false","Biography information for Mr Peter Bone","Wellingborough","Mr Peter Bone","4651"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751248","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-20","<p>A consultation will commence in due course.</p><p />","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-20T14:27:31.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751248/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751248/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751248/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-12","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when his Department plans to provide further details of the proposed new standardised formula to calculate the number of new homes required in any local area.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","4455"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751249","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-17","<p>We are currently considering the responses to the consultation, which closed on 2 May, and will respond in due course.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-17T16:15:34.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751249/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751249/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751249/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-12","Housing Market","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to paragraph A.143 of Fixing Our Broken Housing Market, published on 7 February 2017, when his Department will issue guidance to clarify the meaning of backing of affected local communities.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","4508"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751250","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-19","<p>The Government has an ambitious programme to bring brownfield land back into use in England and is working closely with local authorities to drive this forward. In April 2017 we introduced a requirement for local planning authorities to publish a statutory brownfield land register by the end of 2017 which will identify which previously developed sites are suitable for housing. We are currently working with representative organisations for local government to ensure local planning authorities have these brownfield land registers in place. In addition, there is continuing engagement with local authorities on a range of other programmes, including the designation of 26 Housing Zones on brownfield land, and our £1.2 billion Starter Homes Land Fund to bring forward suitable brownfield land for starter homes and other types of affordable home ownership products.</p><p /><p />","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-19T14:01:25.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751250/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751250/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751250/answer","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751250/answer/previousversion/5093","Biography information for Alok Sharma","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-12","Derelict Land","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what discussions his Department has had with local authorities on the development of brownfield sites for housing in England.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kerr","Stirling","Stephen Kerr","4562"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751251","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-18","<p>Based on the advice of an independent expert group, we are prioritising testing of Aluminium Composite Material cladding. A series of additional system tests have been commissioned as a further step in helping building owners to reach decisions on the best way of keeping their buildings safe.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-18T16:22:14.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751251/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751251/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751251/answer","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751251/answer/previousversion/5090","Biography information for Alok Sharma","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-12","Insulation: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the timetable is for local authorities being permitted to submit for testing at the building Research  Establishment cladding samples that are not of the aluminium composite material construction used on Grenfell Tower.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","4555"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751252","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-17","<p>That information is not held by the Department.</p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-07-17T15:23:32.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751252/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751252/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751252/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-12","Council Tax: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether his Department hold data on the number of councils who have credit card charges in place for payment of council tax by credit card.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","4595"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751253","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-18","<p>The Digital Economy Act 2017 amended S90 of the Consumer Rights Act on secondary ticketing. My Department will be consulting industry; stakeholder and consumer interests to help inform an appropriate update of this guidance.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-07-18T15:15:52.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751253/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751253/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751253/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-12","Tickets: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what plans he has to publish updated guidance on sections 90 to 95 of the Consumer Rights Act 2015 on secondary ticketing.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","4581"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751254","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-18","<p>DCMS, through VisitBritain, has allocated £260,000 in 2016-17 and £240,000 in 2017-18 towards the Mayflower 400 celebrations. Additionally, Mayflower 400 received a £35,000 Arts Council England grant towards the Mayflower Museum in February 2015. Plymouth has received other Arts Council grants which will benefit the celebrations indirectly.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2017-07-18T15:29:55.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751254/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751254/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751254/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-12","Mayflower: Anniversaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how much funding has been allocated to the Mayflower 400 year anniversary celebrations in (a) 2017, (b) 2018, (c) 2019, (d) 2020 and (e) 2021.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","4464"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751255","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-17","<p>A review of gaming machines and social responsibility measures was launched in October 2016, this includes a close look at fixed odds betting terminals. Responses to the review's call for evidence are being considered and a response will be published in due course.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-07-17T13:40:05.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751255/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751255/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751255/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-12","Gaming Machines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, if she will make it her policy to reduce the maximum stake on fixed-odds betting terminals from £100 to £2.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","4523"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751256","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-17","<p>As set out in previous statements to the House, the Secretary of State's quasi-judicial responsibilities in relation to the proposed acquisition of Sky by 21st Century Fox will be discharged, robustly and transparently. Such decisions must also be taken as promptly as is reasonably practicable.</p><p> </p><p>On 29 June the Secretary of State announced that she is minded-to refer the merger to the Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) on media plurality grounds. In coming to a final decision, consideration will be given to the available evidence before her including any further representations received following the call for evidence which closed on 14 July.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-07-17T14:13:33.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751256/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751256/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751256/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-12","21st Century Fox: Sky","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, if she will postpone the Fox takeover of Sky until the second half of the Leveson Inquiry has been completed.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","4661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751257","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-21","<p>This offence will be enacted by secondary legislation. We will be consulting industry and consumer interests to help inform the drafting of this legislation before giving the European Commission and Member States requisite notice, as the offence falls under the Technical Standards Directive. We will then seek a legislative opportunity to table the regulation which has to be approved by both Houses.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-07-21T13:46:14.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751257/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751257/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751257/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-12","Tickets: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what plans she has to implement the power to create an offence of breaching limits on internet and other ticket sales contained in section 106 of the Digital Economy Act 2017.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","4580"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751258","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-21","<p>None.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-07-21T13:44:13.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751258/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751258/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751258/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-12","Radio Frequencies: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment she has made of Ofcom's performance in issuing Wireless Telegraphy Act link licenses.","false","Biography information for Nigel Mills","Amber Valley","Nigel Mills","4694"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751259","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-18","<p>There are currently no plans for 47 Squadron RAF to operate the A400M.</p><p>47 Squadron operates C-130J aircraft whose current planned out of service date is 2035.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-07-18T13:39:52.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751259/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751259/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751259/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-12","Future Large Aircraft: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has to procure A400M aircraft for use by 47 Squadron RAF.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","4689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751260","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-21","<p>The Hercules C-130K model (CMk 1 and Mk3) retired from service on 31 December 2012.The Hercules C-130J CMk4 are scheduled to retire from RAF service on 31 March 2035. The Hercules C-130J CMk5 has begun an approved drawdown plan, and the final aircraft will leave service in 2019.We are procuring the A400M to assume the roles performed by all variants of the Hercules C-130J aircraft.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-07-21T13:55:04.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751260/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751260/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751260/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-12","Hercules Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the planned out of service dates are for the RAF's (a) Hercules C1/C3 (K) and (b) Hercules C4/C5 (J) variants; and what plans his Department has to procure a replacement for those aircraft's specialist capability.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","4690"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751261","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-19","The Ministry of Defence (MOD) routinely publishes statistics on the equipment contracts it places on gov.uk at the following link: https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/mod-trade-industry-and-contracts-2016. The MOD also now publishes a breakdown of expenditure with UK industry. This can also be found on gov.uk: at the following link: https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/mod-regional-expenditure-with-uk-industry-and-supported-employment-201516.","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","4692","2017-07-19T14:38:35.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751261/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751261/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751261/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-12","Ministry of Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which of his Department's programmes procurement contracts have been agreed between his Department and overseas suppliers for work related to the (a) Ships, (b) Submarines, (c) Land, (d) Weapons, (e) Combat Air, (f) Air Support, (g) Helicopters, (h) ISTAR and (j) Information Systems and Services Equipment Plan.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","4691"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751262","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-19","The Ministry of Defence (MOD) routinely publishes statistics on the equipment contracts it places on gov.uk at the following link: https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/mod-trade-industry-and-contracts-2016. The MOD also now publishes a breakdown of expenditure with UK industry. This can also be found on gov.uk: at the following link: https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/mod-regional-expenditure-with-uk-industry-and-supported-employment-201516.","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","4691","2017-07-19T14:38:35.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751262/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751262/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751262/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-12","Ministry of Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many procurement contracts have been agreed between his Department and overseas suppliers for work related to the (a) Ships, (b) Submarines, (c) Land, (d) Weapons, (e) Combat Air, (f) Air Support, (g) Helicopters, (h) ISTAR and (j) Information Systems and Services Equipment Plan; and what the total value is of those contracts.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","4692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751263","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-17","<p>Nine P-8A Poseidon maritime patrol aircraft are being procured for use by the UK Armed Forces, with delivery of the first one expected in 2019. While initial support will be provided in the USA as part of the foreign military sale arrangement with the US Government, work is under way to define the support requirements from 2020 onwards. The opportunities arising from these will be managed through normal procurement routes, and UK businesses will be encouraged to participate in any competitions for this work. In advance of this, two industry days have already been held near Lossiemouth to highlight supply chain opportunities for local businesses.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-07-17T14:09:51.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751263/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751263/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751263/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-12","Maritime Patrol Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of the workshare for support and maintenance contracts for the planned P-8 Poseidon fleet he plans to have fulfilled by UK-based companies.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","4674"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751264","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-21","<p>The Ministry of Defence currently has more than 300 Foreign Military Sales agreements relating to equipment and support, with a total value of just under $12 billion. I am withholding the information as its disclosure would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-07-21T13:40:35.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751264/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751264/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751264/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-12","Ministry of Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for which of his Department's programmes under the Equipment Plan are contracts being procured under the foreign military sales agreement; and what the value is of each of those contracts.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","4693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751265","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-18","<p>The Government and Boeing are working closely together on a long-term initiative to advance prosperity in the UK. Ministers from the Ministry of Defence and the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy are meeting regularly with the company to monitor progress. For example, Boeing and the Government are working together to build a new £100 million P-8A facility at RAF Lossiemouth in Scotland, creating more than 100 new jobs. Boeing has also announced further investments in the UK, including establishing its first European factory in Sheffield. Furthermore, the Government and Boeing are working with UK suppliers to increase opportunities on future global programmes. This includes a recent event in Seattle aimed at showcasing the capabilities of UK companies to Boeing engineers and supply chain managers. A further event will take place in the autumn.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-07-18T13:31:53.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751265/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751265/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751265/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-12","Boeing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that Boeing maximises UK industrial workshare and employment during the delivery of platforms built by that company.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","4675"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751266","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-18","<p>Competition remains the main mechanism for delivering value for money in the defence programme. Our policy of agreeing firm prices, or setting an agreed variation of price formula in our contracts to account for inflation, further incentivises contractors to control costs. Where competition is not possible, we work with our large defence contractors to agree labour rates which are considered reasonable for use in single source contracts. The Single Source Contract Regulations, introduced under the Defence Reform Act (2014), provide the Department with enhanced access to information from a supplier on costs, including labour costs, and an option to take disputes to the Single Source Regulations Office for a legally-binding determination.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-07-18T13:34:57.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751266/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751266/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751266/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-12","Defence: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to reduce inflation in defence labour costs.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","4685"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751267","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-19","<p>The Submarine Delivery Agency (SDA) continues its work to become an Executive Agency of the Ministry of Defence by no later than April 2018. There are currently around 1,300 people working in the SDA and the employment expenditure is approximately £78 million.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-07-19T15:00:11.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751267/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751267/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751267/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-12","Submarine Delivery Body: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many people are employed by his Department's Submarine Delivery Authority; and what the value is of that body's total employment expenditure.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","4686"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751268","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-20","<p>Information on the numbers of Nepali nationals recruited into the Brigade of Gurkhas and UK Regular Forces, by Financial Year (FY), is provided in the following table:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>FY2010-11</p></td><td><p>FY2011-12</p></td><td><p>FY2012-13</p></td><td><p>FY2013-14</p></td><td><p>FY2014-15</p></td><td><p>FY2015-16</p></td><td><p>FY2016-17</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>180</p></td><td><p>180</p></td><td><p>130</p></td><td><p>130</p></td><td><p>240</p></td><td><p>250</p></td><td><p>320</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Note: The vast majority of Nepali national intake is to the Brigade of Gurkhas, with only a small number joining the UK Regulars. Numbers are rounded and do not include Locally Employed Civilians.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-07-20T15:16:18.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751268/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751268/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751268/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-12","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Nepalese citizens were recruited by his Department in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","4687"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751269","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-18","<p>The Armed Forces are working towards a target of 10% of recruits to come from Black, Asian or Minority Ethnic (BAME) backgrounds by 2020, as announced by the previous Prime Minister prior to the 2015 election.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-07-18T13:41:35.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751269/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751269/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751269/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-12","Armed Forces: Ethnic Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what targets his Department has set for the recruitment of ethnic minorities into the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","4688"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751270","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-17","<p>The UK will never sign, ratify or become party to the treaty prohibiting nuclear weapons. We do not believe that it will bring us closer to a world without nuclear weapons as it fails to address the key issues that must first be overcome to achieve lasting global nuclear disarmament. We consider that the best way to achieve a world without nuclear weapons is through gradual multilateral disarmament negotiated using a step-by-step approach within existing international frameworks. The UK continues to work towards global nuclear disarmament through the framework of the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-07-17T14:03:10.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751270/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751270/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751270/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-12","Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to his oral Answer of 10 July 2017, Official Report, column 23, to the hon. Member for North Ayrshire and Arran, for what reasons it is Government policy that the nuclear ban treaty should not apply to the UK.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","4753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751271","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-17","<p>We have sought an initial two year package of support for the 50 AH-64E helicopters from the US Government as part of the Foreign Military Sales agreement. We do not expect to place a contract for the subsequent long-term support services until 2020. Subject to demonstrating value for money, we intend that Boeing Defence UK will be the prime contractor for this work, and we anticipate that the breadth of AH-64E support activities in the UK will be broadly similar to those conducted on the current Apache Mk1. The exact nature of the supply chain will not be determined until much closer to the contract award date.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-07-17T14:01:25.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751271/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751271/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751271/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-12","Apache AH-64 Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what proportion of support and maintenance contracts for the planned UK AH-64E Apache fleet will be fulfilled by UK-based companies.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","4602"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751272","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-17","<p>The UK Government has not undertaken any environmental remediation at the Nevada test site. In 1993, following a report of the Australian Royal Commission on the conduct of British nuclear tests in Australia, the UK Government made an ex gratia payment of £20 million to the Australian Government. This payment was part of a full and final settlement of the UK Government's liability for any claims resulting from the British test programme. The Ministry of Defence has made evaluations of residual contamination on Christmas Island: the last in 1998 concluded that any required remediation had been undertaken. The Ministry of Defence has made no evaluation of the locations from which uranium used in the manufacture of UK nuclear warheads was procured, nor made any environmental remediation.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-07-17T14:30:09.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751272/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751272/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751272/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-12","Nuclear Weapons: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether any environmental remediation to areas contaminated by the testing of British nuclear warheads in (a) the Nevada nuclear test site, (b) Montebello Island, Maralinga and Emu Field, Australia, (c) Malden Island and Kiritimati and (d) any location from which uranium used in the manufacture of nuclear warheads was procured has been carried out.","false","Biography information for Kelvin Hopkins","Luton North","Kelvin Hopkins","4652"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751273","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-19","<p>The names of the Type 26 Frigates will be announced in due course.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-07-19T14:55:27.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751273/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751273/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751273/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-12","Type 26 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he plans to announce the names of the new Type 25 Frigates.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","4466"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751274","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-17","<p>It is too early to provide details of costs related to the re-routing of the South Atlantic air bridge covering items such as fuel, handling and landing fees and these will be tracked and recorded.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-07-17T13:58:53.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751274/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751274/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751274/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-12","Falkland Islands: Air Routes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what costs have been incurred as a result of the re-routing of the South Atlantic air bridge.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","4601"
