"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751354","Department of Health","false","2017-07-21","<p>The Government will work with partners at all levels, including those who use services and who work to provide care, to bring forward proposals for public consultation. The Government will consult on options to encourage a wider debate.</p><p> </p><p>The consultation will set out options to improve the social care system and to put it on a more secure financial footing, supporting people, families and communities to prepare for old age, and address issues related to the quality of care and variation in practice.</p><p> </p><p>We will provide further details on the next steps on social care in due course.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","4698 ; 4704","2017-07-21T09:11:40.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751354/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751354/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751354/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-07-12","Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the timeframe is for the consultation on social care announced in the Queen's Speech 2017.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","4697"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751355","Department of Health","false","2017-07-21","<p>The Government will work with partners at all levels, including those who use services and who work to provide care, to bring forward proposals for public consultation. The Government will consult on options to encourage a wider debate.</p><p> </p><p>The consultation will set out options to improve the social care system and to put it on a more secure financial footing, supporting people, families and communities to prepare for old age, and address issues related to the quality of care and variation in practice.</p><p> </p><p>We will provide further details on the next steps on social care in due course.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","4697 ; 4704","2017-07-21T09:11:40.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751355/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751355/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751355/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-07-12","Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will ensure that funding will be central to the consultation on social care announced in the Queen's Speech 2017.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","4698"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751356","Department of Health","false","2017-07-17","<p>Section 136 of the Mental Health Act is a power reserved for police officers only. The information is not available in the format requested.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","4739","2017-07-17T15:45:50.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751356/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751356/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/751356/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-07-12","Compulsorily Detained Psychiatric Patients","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 11 July 2017 to Question 3341, how many people were detained under section 136 of the Mental Health Act 1983 broken down by the job role of the person who carried out the section in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","4738"
